src/lib/components/blockie.react.js.description:
ExampleComponent is an example component.
It takes a property, `label`, and
displays it.
It renders an input with the property `value`
which is editable by the user.

id.description:
The ID of this component, used to identify dash components
in callbacks. The ID needs to be unique across all of the
components in an app.

className.description: Often used with CSS to style elements with common properties.

key.description:
A unique identifier for the component, used to improve
performance by React.js while rendering components
See https://reactjs.org/docs/lists-and-keys.html for more info

See https://reactjs.org/docs/lists-and-keys.html for more info

color.description:
Card color, options: primary, secondary, success, info, warning, danger,
light, dark. Default is light.

body.description:
Apply the `card-body` class to the card, so that there is no need to also
include a CardBody component in the children of this Card. Default: False

outline.description: Apply color styling to just the border of the card.

inverse.description: Invert text colours for use with a darker background.

is_loading.name: bool
is_loading.description: Determines if the component is loading or not

component_name.name: string
component_name.description: Holds the name of the component that is loading

loading_state.description: Object that holds the loading state object coming from dash-renderer
